### Methods
- A method is a block of code in a program that Perform specifiic Task.
- It can take input value (Parameters), perform operation and return this.
                    ↓
                    ↓
** There are Foru types of Method 
                    ↓
- 1. Methods without parameters and without values
- 2. Methods with Parammeterrs and without values
- 3. Methods without Parameterrs and but return values
- 4. Methods without Parameterrs and but return values

## Syntax of Methods
                ↓
return_type method Name(Parameters)
{
     //Boundry of the Method
     // Method Definition
}

--> void:- Empty Function
--> static method :- Belong to class not an objects
--> Return:- Whenever you see the return control will leave immediately the program.

Note:- If you are calling the method inside the main method the called method should be static method.

Parameter --> is a Placehoder in amethod definition that specifies the what input needs.
Arguments --> is actual value passed during the method call.
Local Variable:- is decleared inside method, constructor, block of code. only accessible with in specific method or block
Instance VAriables:- is declared inside only class but out side any method

### Comments
--> a bit of text compliler will ignore 
--> // single line comments
--> /*-------*/ mulltiline comments
--> /**------**/ genrates documents of your code
